# Container image CVE exceptions — v8.0.0
# Reviewed: 2026-05-19  |  Re-review: each release cycle
# All entries are base-image (bitnami/minideb:bookworm) CVEs with no
# upstream fix available in Debian bookworm. Trivy status column is
# "affected" or "will_not_fix" for each.
# See docs/security-review.md#container-image-scanning for full rationale.

# zlib1g CVE-2023-45853 — CRITICAL, Debian will_not_fix
# Integer overflow in inflate(). Only exploitable when processing
# attacker-controlled deflate streams with a specific window size.
# curl and git in this image decompress only trusted responses from
# operator-configured remotes. Not network-exposed via datawatch APIs.
CVE-2023-45853

# libgnutls30 — no fix in bookworm (5 CVEs across CRITICAL and HIGH)
# datawatch uses Go crypto/tls, not gnutls; gnutls is pulled transitively
# by curl and git. None of these affect the datawatch TLS listener.
#   CVE-2026-33845 (CRITICAL): DTLS zero-length DoS. Container runs no
#     DTLS listener; not reachable.
#   CVE-2026-42010 (CRITICAL): Auth bypass via NUL in cert CN. Only
#     triggerable by a malicious TLS server; git/curl connect only to
#     operator-configured remotes.
#   CVE-2026-33846 (HIGH): heap buffer overflow in DTLS. Same surface
#     as CVE-2026-33845; unreachable without DTLS listener.
#   CVE-2026-3833 (HIGH): policy bypass via case-sensitive comparison.
#     Affects cert policy enforcement; mitigated by use of trusted CAs.
#   CVE-2026-42011 (HIGH): security bypass via incorrect name matching.
#     Same mitigation as CVE-2026-3833.
CVE-2026-33845
CVE-2026-42010
CVE-2026-33846
CVE-2026-3833
CVE-2026-42011

# libsqlite3-0 CVE-2025-7458 — CRITICAL, no fix in bookworm
# Integer overflow in SQLite. Used internally by the gh CLI binary;
# not exposed via datawatch REST/MCP APIs. Only processes trusted
# local state, not attacker-supplied SQL.
CVE-2025-7458

# curl / libcurl4 — no fix in bookworm (2 HIGH)
#   CVE-2026-5773: Wrong file transfer via SMB protocol. SMB is not
#     used by curl in this image (no SMB server configured).
#   CVE-2026-6276: Cookie leak on cross-origin redirect. curl is used
#     by agent tooling for REST API calls; operator-configured endpoints.
CVE-2026-5773
CVE-2026-6276

# libldap-2.5-0 CVE-2023-2953 — HIGH, no fix in bookworm
# Null pointer dereference in ber_memalloc_x via malformed LDAP response.
# OpenLDAP not directly used; pulled transitively by OpenSSH. No LDAP
# connections made from within the container.
CVE-2023-2953

# ncurses CVE-2025-69720 — HIGH, no fix in bookworm
# (affects libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base)
# Buffer overflow in terminal escape sequence parsing. Triggerable only
# by attacker-controlled terminal output inside a tmux session. Requires
# prior container shell access.
CVE-2025-69720

# libssh2-1 CVE-2026-7598 — HIGH, no fix in bookworm
# Integer overflow in username/password handling. libssh2 is used by
# git for SSH transport. Only triggerable by a malicious SSH server;
# git SSH remotes are operator-configured, not attacker-controlled.
CVE-2026-7598

# libgcrypt20 CVE-2026-41989 — HIGH, no fix in bookworm
# DoS / buffer overflow in gnupg crypto backend. gnupg is used for
# package signature verification during apt installs (build-time only).
# Not present in the runtime attack surface of a deployed container.
CVE-2026-41989
